description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d . I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler. Create a class in a subpackage such as:

package subpackage;

public class Test {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }

}

Then compile using the following command: ajc subpackage\Test.java. You will see a directory "subpackage" created under the existing "subpackage" directory.

Executing the java command results in an Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: subpackage/Test. Running either of the following commands fixes the problem: ajc -d .
